This paper deals with word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and machine translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. 

The paper also involves experimental approaches and machine learning models, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of word embeddings and their relation to word frequency and co-occurrence noise, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
